<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="589" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,331,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus has a distinct epiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[737,858,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[166,1391,739,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@4.[160,1427,739,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia. A–C. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. D–F. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A, D. Dorsal view. B, E. Lateral view. C, F. Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417207/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
). Epiphallic median lobe scimitar-like, and the apex curved outward. Epiphallic lateral lobe nearly shaped as a rectangular. The sclerotized portion of ectoparamere sickle-like, tapering and apically obtuse.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="589" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,331,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" box="[808,1284,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[808,933,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K." box="[940,1284,475,502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="5 - 230" refId="ref2341" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K. (1893) Revision du systeme des orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Series 2, 13, 5 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article" year="1893">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but varies in male genitalia traits. The epiphallic lateral lobe of this new genus is slightly rectangular in shape and armed with a truncated tip, and the ectoparamere is sickle-shaped. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" box="[743,868,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[743,868,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand, has a rod-like epiphallic lateral lobe and a truncated ectoparamere apex (Asian species, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="He et al. 2010" authorityName="He" authorityYear="2010" box="[862,1297,583,610]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis box="[862,1116,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus bispinosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="He, Z. Q. &amp; Li, K. &amp; Fang, Y. &amp; Liu, X. W." box="[1126,1297,583,610]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="55 - 62" refId="ref2641" refString="He, Z. Q., Li, K., Fang, Y. &amp; Liu, X. W. (2010) A taxonomic study of the genus Amusurgus Brunner von Wanttenwyl from China (Orthoptera, Gryllidae, Trigonidiinae). Zootaxa, 2423 (1), 55 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2423.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
He 
<emphasis box="[1169,1229,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus fulvus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K." box="[224,562,619,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="5 - 230" refId="ref2341" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K. (1893) Revision du systeme des orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Series 2, 13, 5 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article" year="1893">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tan, 2022" authorityName="Tan" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,964,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulus">
<emphasis box="[619,846,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus caerulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, M. K." box="[852,964,619,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="453 - 463" refId="ref2748" refString="Tan, M. K. (2022) A new aboreal species of sword-tailed cricket (Orthoptera: Trigonidiidae: Trigonidiinae) from the mangrove in Singapore. Zootaxa, 5092 (4), 453 - 463. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5092.4.4" type="journal article" year="2022">Tan, 2022</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) or a finger-like epiphallic lateral lobe and median lobe (Australian species, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" box="[587,1103,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanyakis">
<emphasis box="[587,818,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus kanyakis</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minmirri">
<emphasis box="[1116,1349,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus minmirri</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" box="[398,896,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilarius">
<emphasis box="[398,617,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus nilarius</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
